NOTICE
======

Prewalk Technique Attribution
------------------------------

The prewalk technique implemented by this repository was published by:

    Can Bölük / Stencil
    "You only need the frontier model for one single edit"
    2026-07-13
    https://stencil.so/blog/prewalk

Stencil upstreamed the technique to omp, where it ships natively as
`--prewalk`, `--prewalk-into <model>`, or `/prewalk`.

This repository is an independent implementation that extends the published
technique with:

- One-completed-task semantics (edit + verification, not just a scaffold edit)
- A structured PAUSE checkpoint todo for human review at the handoff
- A frontier-phase turn budget grounded in the article's behavioral findings
- Executor anti-premature-completion rules
- Frontend verification recipes (Playwright desktop screenshots, DOM geometry
  probes, CSS animation cost diagnosis)
- A task-selection rubric and worked scouting procedure
- Hermes Agent bindings (slash command, skill packaging)

